The paper focuses on using Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for offline handwritten signature verification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve performance, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of the system to forgeries, which falls under the subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the analysis of the feature space learned by the model, which falls under the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
